properties.headline: High Wind Warning issued January 6 at 1:55PM MST until January 7 at 5:00AM MST by NWS Riverton WY
properties.description:
...High winds likely this afternoon through Monday night...

* WHAT...Southwest winds 25 to 40 mph with gusts up to 60 mph
expected. Higher wind gusts to around 70 mph are possible near
Clark. The winds have already gusted to 43 mph at the airport
just east of Cody at 1220 PM this afternoon.

* WHERE...Cody Foothills, especially in the vicinity of Clark.

* WHEN...From 2 PM this afternoon to 5 AM MST Tuesday.

* IMPACTS...Travel will be difficult, especially for high
profile vehicles, especially along Highway 120 near Clark.
properties.instruction:
Use caution of traveling. Please keep two hands on your steering
wheel in case of a sudden, strong wind gust. In a parking lot,
park into the wind to minimize the possibility of your car door
hitting another parked vehicle.

NWSheadline: HIGH WIND WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 5 AM MST TUESDAY
